import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of GitHub activity during the recorded period?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('GitHub Activity Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of GitHub activity counts?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    hourly_average = data.groupby('hour')['count'].mean()
    
    ax = hourly_average.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average number of GitHub activities per hour?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')

    plt.scatter(data['hour'], data['count'])

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    plt.title('What is the correlation between time of day and GitHub activity?')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    data['day_of_week'] = data['time'].dt.day_name()
    day_counts = data.groupby('day_of_week')['count'].sum().reindex(['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'])
    
    day_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of GitHub activity by day of the week?")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
